In [234]:
from sklearn import neural_network
from sklearn.compose import ColumnTransformer
from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline
from sklearn.impute import SimpleImputer
from sklearn.preprocessing import OneHotEncoder
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from sklearn import linear_model
import sklearn

def createPipeLine(X, model):
  # Preprocessing for numerical data
  numerical_transformer = SimpleImputer(strategy='median')

  # Preprocessing for categorical data
  categorical_transformer = Pipeline(steps=[
      ('imputer', SimpleImputer(strategy='most_frequent')),
      ('onehot', OneHotEncoder(handle_unknown='ignore'))
  ])


  numerical_cols = [cname for cname in X.columns if X[cname].dtype in ['int64', 'float64']]
  categorical_cols = [cname for cname in X.columns if X[cname].nunique() < 10 and 
                      X[cname].dtype == "object"]


  # Bundle preprocessing for numerical and categorical data
  preprocessor = ColumnTransformer(
      transformers=[
          ('num', numerical_transformer, numerical_cols),
          ('cat', categorical_transformer, categorical_cols)
      ])

  #model = linear_model.SGDClassifier(loss='log', alpha=0, learning_rate='constant', eta0=0.01)


  my_pipeline = Pipeline(steps=[('preprocessor', preprocessor),
                                ('Scaler', StandardScaler()),
                                ('model', model)
                              ])
  return my_pipeline
In [235]:
t = train_data["Survived"]
X = train_data.drop(labels=['Survived'],axis=1)
X_train, X_validation, t_train, t_validation = sklearn.model_selection.train_test_split(X, t, test_size=0.2, random_state=2)

model = linear_model.SGDClassifier(loss='log', alpha=0, learning_rate='constant', eta0=0.01)
my_pipeline = createPipeLine(X_train, model)
my_pipeline.fit(X_train, t_train)
print('Accuracy score on train', my_pipeline.score(X_train, t_train))
print('Accuracy score on validation', my_pipeline.score(X_validation, t_validation))
preds = my_pipeline.predict(test_data)
output = pd.DataFrame({'PassengerId': test_passengerID, 'Survived': preds})

from sklearn.preprocessing import OneHotEncoder

encoder = None


def doOHE(df, cols):
  global encoder
  if encoder is None:
    OH_encoder = OneHotEncoder(handle_unknown='ignore', sparse=False)
    OH_encoder = OH_encoder.fit(df[cols])
    encoder = OH_encoder  
  OH_cols = pd.DataFrame(encoder.transform(df[cols]))
  OH_cols.columns = encoder.get_feature_names(cols)
  OH_cols.index = df.index

  df = df.drop(cols,axis=1)
  df = pd.concat([df, OH_cols],axis=1)
  return df

train_data = doOHE(train_data,['Sex','Embarked'])
test_data = doOHE(test_data,['Sex','Embarked'])

print("Done One Hot Encoding")

def addFeatures(df):
  df["Underage"] = (df['Age'] < 18).map({False:0.0,True:1.0})
  df["TotalFamily"] = df['SibSp'] + df['Parch']
  df['IsAlone'] = (df['TotalFamily'] == 0).map({False:0.0,True:1.0})
  df['Age_Squared'] = df['Age']**2
  return df

train_data = addFeatures(train_data)
test_data = addFeatures(test_data)
print("Done Adding Features")



     


















    
    






Done Adding Features

from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler

scaler = None


def doScale(df):
  global scaler
  if scaler is None:
    scaler = StandardScaler()
    scaler = scaler.fit(df)
  colNames = df.columns
  df = pd.DataFrame(columns=colNames, data=scaler.transform(df))
  return df

train_data_ex3 = train_data
test_data_ex3 = test_data
train_data = doScale(train_data)
test_data = doScale(test_data)

from sklearn import metrics
alpha = [0,1e-4, 1e-3, 1e-2, 1e-1, 1e0]
eta = [0.003,0.006,0.009,0.012,0.015,0.018,0.021,0.024,0.027,0.03]

best_et = 0

for alp in alpha:
  for et in eta:
    model = linear_model.SGDClassifier(loss='log', alpha=alp, learning_rate='constant',random_state=2, eta0=et)
    model.fit(X_train, t_train)
    y_train_prob = model.predict_proba(X_train)
    y_validation_prob = model.predict_proba(X_validation)
    
    score = model.score(X_validation, t_validation)
    accArr += [score]
    score = metrics.log_loss(t_validation, y_validation_prob)
    ceArr += [score]
    
    if score < best_acc:
      best_et = et
      best_alp = alp
      best_acc = score

My Score¶











Summary¶
At this task I practiced for the first time to use Sklearn libraries.

I started first by copying a lot of guides and created a pipeline to handle all of the job for me.

I felt that using the pipeline was cool experience but at the same time I wanted to try the alternate option of transforming my data step by step, thus I recreated my notebook with the prior knowledge I had.


I had trouble understanding what parameters I should change at the SGD model, at the end to my surprise my changing of parameters did in fact help my model score better at kaggle's competition.


I was using some notebooks as refernces here


    

  • First the very helpful introduction to Titanic notebook I found
    
https://www.kaggle.com/alexisbcook/getting-started-with-titanic
    • 

  • Second I found a very detailed notebook and saw how he did his feature engineering
    
https://www.kaggle.com/gunesevitan/titanic-advanced-feature-engineering-tutorial
    • 

  • A surprsingly helpful site I found was one about statistics about titanic survivors, that apart from helping me better understand the subjet of the task was really interesting.
    
http://www.icyousee.org/titanic.html
    • 



Kaggle's two courses about machine learning were too really helpful.

from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix
# calculate score and loss from cv (KFold or LPO) and display graphs
def get_cv_score_and_loss(X, t, model, transformer=None, k=None, p=None, show_score_loss_graphs=False, use_pbar=True, averageMatrix=True, printRes=False):
    scores_losses_df = pd.DataFrame(columns=['fold_id', 'split', 'score', 'loss', 'TN', 'FP', 'FN', 'TP'])

    if k is not None:
        cv = KFold(n_splits=k, shuffle=True, random_state=1)
    elif p is not None:
        cv = LeavePOut(p)
    else:
        raise ValueError('you need to specify k or p in order for the cv to work')

    if use_pbar:
        pbar = tqdm(desc='Computing Models', total=find_generator_len(cv.split(X)))

    for i, (train_ids, val_ids) in enumerate(cv.split(X)):
        X_train = X.loc[train_ids]
        t_train = t.loc[train_ids]
        X_val = X.loc[val_ids]
        t_val = t.loc[val_ids]

        model.fit(X_train, t_train)

        y_train = model.predict(X_train)
        y_val = model.predict(X_val)
        tn_train, fp_train, fn_train, tp_train = confusion_matrix(t_train, y_train).ravel()
        tn_val, fp_val, fn_val, tp_val = confusion_matrix(t_val, y_val).ravel()
        scores_losses_df.loc[len(scores_losses_df)] = [i, 'train', model.score(X_train, t_train), metrics.log_loss(t_train, y_train),tn_train, fp_train, fn_train, tp_train]
        scores_losses_df.loc[len(scores_losses_df)] = [i, 'val', model.score(X_val, t_val), metrics.log_loss(t_val, y_val),tn_val, fp_val, fn_val, tp_val]

        if use_pbar:
            pbar.update()

    if use_pbar:
        pbar.close()

    val_scores_losses_df = scores_losses_df[scores_losses_df['split']=='val']
    train_scores_losses_df = scores_losses_df[scores_losses_df['split']=='train']

    mean_val_score = val_scores_losses_df['score'].mean()
    mean_val_loss = val_scores_losses_df['loss'].mean()
    mean_train_score = train_scores_losses_df['score'].mean()
    mean_train_loss = train_scores_losses_df['loss'].mean()
    mean_train_tn = round(train_scores_losses_df['TN'].mean())
    mean_train_fp = round(train_scores_losses_df['FP'].mean())
    mean_train_fn = round(train_scores_losses_df['FN'].mean())
    mean_train_tp = round(train_scores_losses_df['TP'].mean())
    mean_val_tn = round(val_scores_losses_df['TN'].mean())
    mean_val_fp = round(val_scores_losses_df['FP'].mean())
    mean_val_fn = round(val_scores_losses_df['FN'].mean())
    mean_val_tp = round(val_scores_losses_df['TP'].mean())

    if show_score_loss_graphs:
        fig = px.line(scores_losses_df, x='fold_id', y='score', color='split', title=f'Mean Val Score: {mean_val_score:.2f}, Mean Train Score: {mean_train_score:.2f}')
        fig.show()
        fig = px.line(scores_losses_df, x='fold_id', y='loss', color='split', title=f'Mean Val Loss: {mean_val_loss:.2f}, Mean Train Loss: {mean_train_loss:.2f}')
        fig.show()
    if averageMatrix:
      print("Average TN,FP,FN,TP of train")
      print(' {:4d}'.format(mean_train_tn), " | ", '{:4d}'.format(mean_train_fp), "\n", '{:4d}'.format(mean_train_fn), " | ", '{:4d}'.format(mean_train_tp))
      print()
      print("Average TN,FP,FN,TP of val")
      print(' {:4d}'.format(mean_val_tn), " | ", '{:4d}'.format(mean_val_fp), "\n", '{:4d}'.format(mean_val_fn), " | ", '{:4d}'.format(mean_val_tp))
    if printRes:
      print(f'mean cv val score: {mean_val_score:.2f}')
      #print(f'\nmean cv val loss {mean_val_loss:.2f}')
      print(f'mean cv train score: {mean_train_score:.2f}')
      #print(f'\nmean cv train loss {mean_train_loss:.2f}')
    return mean_val_score, mean_val_loss, mean_train_score, mean_train_loss

# find generator length

def find_generator_len(generator, use_pbar=True):
    i = 0
    
    if use_pbar:
        pbar = tqdm(desc='Calculating Length', ncols=1000, bar_format='{desc}{bar:10}{r_bar}')

    for a in generator:
        i += 1

        if use_pbar:
            pbar.update()

    if use_pbar:
        pbar.close()

    return i

# calculate precision, recall, specificity, fpr and accuracy
def precision(cm):
    tn, fp, fn, tp = cm.ravel()
    return tp/(tp+fp)

def recall(cm):
    tn, fp, fn, tp = cm.ravel()
    return tp/(tp+fn)

def specificity(cm):
    tn, fp, fn, tp = cm.ravel()
    return tn/(tn+fp)

def fpr(cm):
    tn, fp, fn, tp = cm.ravel()
    return fp/(fp+tn)

def accuracy(cm):
    tn, fp, fn, tp = cm.ravel()
    return (tp+tn)/(tp+tn+fp+fn)
# calculate f1 and balanced accuracy
def f1(cm):
    precision_calc = precision(cm)
    recall_calc = recall(cm)
    return (2*precision_calc*recall_calc)/(precision_calc+recall_calc)

def balanced_accuracy(cm):
    recall_calc = recall(cm)
    specificity_calc = specificity(cm)
    return (recall_calc+specificity_calc)/2


print(f'Train: precision {precision(cm_train):.2f}, recall {recall(cm_train):.2f}, specificity {specificity(cm_train):.2f}, fpr {fpr(cm_train):.2f}, accuracy {accuracy(cm_train):.2f}')
print(f'Train: f1 {f1(cm_train):.2f}, balanced_accuracy {balanced_accuracy(cm_train):.2f}')
